<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES -
        Cylinder Head Assembly - Install Valve Lever
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Install Valve Lever</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, make sure the copper end of the push rods are up before proceeding. Then
                    insert the other end into the hydraulic roller lifter seats before installing the valve lever
                    assemblies.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the crankshaft until the vibration damper notch is 15&#176; from vertical (11 o'clock
                position when viewed from the rear of the engine). This positions all pistons below TDC so the valves
                cannot contact the pistons when tightening the valve lever assemblies.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200470" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2670.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Valve Lever Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Push Rod Assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Lever Assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Lever Mounting Bolt</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the valve lever assemblies and bolts with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the valve lever assemblies in their original locations over the cylinder head mounting
                pads. Install retaining bolts finger tight.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the valve lever mounting bolts to the special torque value.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
